Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1%sachet}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2%unit}. Cut the @medium tomato{1%unit} into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine a good squeeze of lemon juice with the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set your salad dressing aside.

Pat the @sea bass fillets{2} dry with #kitchen paper{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Lay the fish onto a lined baking tray. Spread the @pesto{32%grams} over the top of the fish, then sprinkle over half the lemon zest.

When the potatoes have 12 mins left, bake the fish on the middle shelf until cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the salsa.

Once hot, add the tomato chunks and cook until just warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Gently stir in the garlic and remaining lemon zest and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Squeeze in some lemon juice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Taste and season again if needed, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%grams} to your salad dressing and toss to coat.

Transfer the pesto sea bass to your plates and spoon over the warm tomato salsa. Serve with the rosemary potatoes and salad alongside. Enjoy!